Package: tidybari
Type: Package
Title: Access Boston Area Research Initiative Data
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Josh Rosen
Maintainer: Josh Rosen <rosen.jos@northeastern.edu>
Description: Download and work with data from the Boston Area Research
    Initiative (BARI) Data Portal, hosted on Harvard Dataverse. Provides
    tidy access to neighborhood ecometrics, administrative records, and
    spatial geometries for the City of Boston. Inspired by the tidycensus
    package.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/joshrrosen/tidybari
BugReports: https://github.com/joshrrosen/tidybari/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.1
Imports:
    dataverse,
    tibble,
    dplyr,
    readr,
    sf,
    rlang,
    cli,
    rappdirs,
    magrittr
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    ggplot2,
    rmapshaper,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
Config/testthat/edition: 3
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Depends: 
    R (>= 2.10)
